<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:182px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Bigpond_internet_Satellite.jpg" class="image" title="A foldable Bigpond Satellite Internet dish."><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/18/Bigpond_internet_Satellite.jpg/180px-Bigpond_internet_Satellite.jpg" width="180" height="135" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Bigpond_internet_Satellite.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
A foldable <a href="/wiki/Bigpond" title="Bigpond" class="mw-redirect">Bigpond</a> Satellite Internet dish.</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><b>Satellite Internet services</b> are used in locations where terrestrial <a href="/wiki/Internet" title="Internet">Internet</a> access is not available and in locations which move frequently. Internet access via <a href="/wiki/Satellite" title="Satellite">satellite</a> is available <a href="/wiki/World" title="World">worldwide</a>, including vessels at sea and mobile land vehicles.</p>
